/PG614/XX/PR
/KAPIRKEY HALLEL / SELECTIONS FROM HALLEL/PR
/ITHallel is a required part of the Festival morning service, where Hallel is introduced by a
/MDberah/±ah/XX. As a beloved part of the Festival liturgy that conveys its joyous mood, Hallel
selections can be sung without the /MDberah/±ah/XX at any other time. It is suggested that the Hallel
psalms included here be recited after the /MDAmidah/XX in the Festival evening service. Otherwise
continue with Kaddish Titkabal (page 624) or Festival Kiddush (page 626)./PR
/PR
When Israel went forth out of Egypt,/PR
House of Jacob from the people of a foreign tongue,/PR
/PR
Judah became GodÚs holy place,/PR
Israel became GodÚs seat of rule./PR
/PR
The Sea beheld and fled,/PR
the Jordan turned, reversed its flow./PR
/PR
The mountains danced about like rams,/PR
the hills, like flocks of lambs./PR
/PR
WhatÚs wrong with you, O Sea, that you should flee?/PR
And you, O Jordan, that you turn around?/PR
/PR
You mountains, why do you rejoice like rams,/PR
you hills, like flocks of lambs?/PR
/PR
Tremble, earth, before the mighty one,/PR
before the God of Jacob,/PR
/PR
who turns the rock into a pool of water,/PR
the flint into a bubbling fount!/PR
Psalm 114/XX/PR
